                                                                  4853 1451
 THERMAL,RESOLVED, AND UNRESOLVED REGIONS                       &&4853 1451
 Evaluation  by S.F.Mughabghab   March,2006 (BNL)               &&4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
  RESOLVED RESONANCES in MLBW                                     4853 1451
   Resonance parameters and thermal cross sections of Cd-115m     4853 1451
   (44.6d half-life) not reported[Mu06].An educated guess of a    4853 1451
   thermal capture cross section of 5 barns is deduced.           4853 1451
   An average level spacing for s-wave resonances, 92 eV, is      4853 1451
   computed with the aid of the Gilbert-Cameron formula and the   4853 1451
   associated parameters reported in [Mu06].An average capture    4853 1451
   widths of 82 meV and 134 meV for s- and p-wave resonances      4853 1451
   are deduced respectively  with the  aid of the                 4853 1451
   Mughabghab-Dunford model [Mu00]and systematics.                4853 1451
   Pickett-fence s- and p- wave resonances with average spacings  4853 1451
   of 115 eV and 58 eV  obeying  Porter-Thomas distributions      4853 1451
   with respective neutron strength functions of 0.4 and 3.0 in   4853 1451
   units of 10**-4 are postulated.                                4853 1451
   One bound level is invoked to represent an assumed capture     4853 1451
   capture cross section of 5.0 b.                                4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
   An effective scattering radius of 6.20 fm is adoptted [Mu06]   4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
  Calculated thermal cross sections & resonance integrals*:     &&4853 1451
      ---------------------------------------------             &&4853 1451
      Reaction       Cross section    Res. integral             &&4853 1451
                        (barn)           (barn)                 &&4853 1451
      Total           9.92000E+00           -                   &&4853 1451
      Elastic         4.92000E+00           -                   &&4853 1451
      Capture         5.00000E+00      8.90E+00                 &&4853 1451
      ---------------------------------------------             &&4853 1451
       * Values are to be considered with caution.                4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
  UNRESOLVED RESONANCES in 'energy-dependent parameters'          4853 1451
     (LRF=2) format.                                              4853 1451
   <D0>, <D1>, and ,<D2> are  calculated as described above.      4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
   S0, S1, S2 from the systematicsas reported in [Mu06].          4853 1451
   <Gg0>, <Gg1> <Gg2>  from the systematics described in [Mu06].  4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
   An effective scattering radius of 6.40 fm is adoptted [Mu06]   4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
   Energy- and J-dependence of level spacing were calculated      4853 1451
     according to the Gilbert-Cameron's level density formula with4853 1451
     associated parameters from Mughabghab [Mu06].                4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
