 FAST ENERGY REGION                                             &&4853 1451
 Evaluation: M.Herman, P.Oblozinsky, B.Sarer, March 2006, (BNL) &&4853 1451
                                                                &&4853 1451
 EVALUATION PROCEDURE                                             4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                4853 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               4853 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              4853 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b33 by                    4853 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               4853 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               4853 1451
 and features:                                                    4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 4853 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         4853 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    4853 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              4853 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                4853 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      4853 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   4853 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                4853 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               4853 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      4853 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 4853 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                4853 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   4853 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                4853 1451
   discrete transitions                                           4853 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              4853 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                4853 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               4853 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              4853 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 4853 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              4853 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           4853 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    4853 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 4853 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                4853 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      4853 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        4853 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
 PARAMETERIZATIONS                                                4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
 Following models and parameters were used in the                 4853 1451
 current evaluation:                                              4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
 Discrete levels were taken from the RIPL-2 level                 4853 1451
 file, based on the 1998 version of ENSDF.                        4853 1451
 EMPIRE-specific level densities                                  4853 1451
 MSD calculations with ORION+TRISTAN                              4853 1451
 Heidelberg MSC calculations                                      4853 1451
 Exciton model calculations with code DEGAS                       4853 1451
 Exciton model calculations with code PCROSS                      4853 1451
 Cluster emission in terms of the Iwamoto-Harada model with       4853 1451
 Kalbach systematics angular distributions (see RIPL-1)           4853 1451
 Mean free path parameter in PCROSS set to  1.0 (Recommended ~1.5)4853 1451
 Target excited to the level #2                                   4853 1451
 E1 strength function set to MLO1                                 4853 1451
 GDR parameters from RIPL-2/Exp.data+Plujko systematics           4853 1451
                                                                  4853 1451
